On Sun, 17 Mar 2002, Nemo, the Bus Captain wrote:

> Just noticing that Agilis 61 has a load rating of
> 1700 lbs at 50 psi.  Probably lower if set at 40
> psi for the rear and 33 psi for the front, right?
>  It's the tire pressure that carries the load,
> right?  So lower pressure equals lower load.
> Most of the other "C" rated tires have 1450-1500
> psi at 50 psi load ratings.

The pressure specified by VW is that which will give best handling and
wear on the stock size tires.  If you go to a different size tire, you
need to figure out the correct pressure to carry the specific wheel load
on that tire.  If you don't you will likely get unusual wear or odd
handling.

George Lyle

